TICKET MKT-003 — Persona content system
Ticket ID

MKT-003

Title

Persona content system (Homeowner / Buyer / Realtor) + homepage wiring

Objective

Implement a single source of truth for persona-specific marketing copy and calculator labeling so the homepage can switch between Homeowner, Buyer, Realtor without hardcoding text across components. This enables fast iteration and prevents agent drift.

This ticket must wire the persona toggle so it updates:

Hero headline/subhead + CTAs

Value prop cards

Calculator input labels (not the logic yet)

Output “hero metric” label placeholders

Non-goals

No HubSpot integration yet

No real calculator math yet (MKT-005)

No email gate yet (MKT-004)

No investor persona (explicitly excluded for MVP)

Preconditions

MKT-001 completed (repo deploys)

MKT-002 completed (shadcn/ui + UI kit primitives exist)

Dark mode + cyan accent theme established in tokens

Frozen spec exists: docs/marketing-homepage-spec.md

Implementation Requirements
A) Define persona types and defaults

Create a strongly typed persona enum:

homeowner

buyer

realtor

Default persona on first load: homeowner (unless overridden by querystring; see optional below).

B) Create persona content map (authoritative)

Create file:

src/content/personas.ts

It must export:

PERSONAS list (for tabs)

personaContent object keyed by persona

Each persona must include these fields:

type PersonaKey = "homeowner" | "buyer" | "realtor";

type PersonaContent = {
  key: PersonaKey;
  navLabel: string;

  hero: {
    eyebrow?: string;
    headline: string;
    subheadline: string;
    primaryCtaLabel: string;
    secondaryCtaLabel: string;
  };

  valueProps: Array<{
    title: string;
    body: string;
  }>;

  calculator: {
    title: string;
    description: string;

    // shared inputs labels
    labels: {
      propertyValue: string;
      upfront: string;
      monthly: string;
      horizonYears: string;
      appreciationRate: string;
    };

    // persona-specific optional input labels (placeholders for later tickets)
    optionalLabels: {
      homeownerCashOut?: string;    // homeowner only
      buyerTargetOwnership?: string; // buyer only
      realtorReferralFlat?: string;  // realtor only
      realtorSharePct?: string;      // realtor only
    };

    // hero output labels (placeholders)
    heroMetric: {
      label: string;
      helperText: string;
    };
  };

  howItWorks: {
    steps: Array<{ title: string; body: string }>;
  };

  trust: {
    bullets: string[]; // compliance-friendly
  };
};


Copy tone requirements:

friendly, confident, not salesy

avoid regulated terms like “guaranteed returns”

use “scenario,” “estimates,” “terms summary”

avoid “investment” language on public pages

C) Persona toggle component (stateful)

Create component:

src/components/persona/PersonaTabs.tsx

Requirements:

uses shadcn/ui Tabs

updates persona state

accessible keyboard navigation

visible, simple

D) Wire persona state through homepage sections

Update src/app/page.tsx to:

store persona state at page level (React state)

pass persona content down to:

Hero

ValueProps

CalculatorShell (placeholder)

HowItWorks

Trust section

Create (or update) these section components (if not already present):

src/components/sections/HeroSection.tsx

src/components/sections/ValuePropsSection.tsx

src/components/sections/CalculatorSection.tsx (UI only; no math)

src/components/sections/HowItWorksSection.tsx

src/components/sections/TrustSection.tsx

Each section must accept the relevant portion of PersonaContent and render from it.

E) Optional: querystring override (recommended for marketing links)

Support ?persona=buyer / ?persona=realtor / ?persona=homeowner:

on load, read persona param

set initial persona

ignore invalid values

This is useful for persona-specific ads and links.

Acceptance Criteria (Definition of Done)

Persona toggle visibly switches between Homeowner/Buyer/Realtor

When toggled, the following content changes:

Hero headline + subheadline + CTA labels

Value prop cards (3) content

Calculator title/description and relevant input labels

Trust bullets

Default persona is homeowner

No duplicated persona copy scattered across JSX files

npm run build and Vercel deploy succeed

Optional: ?persona=buyer sets persona correctly (if implemented)

QA Checklist

 Persona toggle works on mobile

 Copy stays compliant (no “guaranteed return” language)

 Tone is consistent and minimal

 No console errors

 All strings live in src/content/personas.ts

Deliverables

src/content/personas.ts with complete content for 3 personas

PersonaTabs component

Homepage sections wired to persona content map

Updated homepage renders correctly in both light and dark mode
